2026-04-20T14:08:15.007+00:00 The tool is scoped to index operations. Based on what I know — 500M rows, columns `user_id`, `order_date`, `amount`, `status`, and only a PK index — the most impactful indexes for order-related queries are clear:

1. **`user_id`** — "show me orders for this user" is the most common order query pattern
2. **`status`** — filtering by order status (pending, shipped, etc.) is extremely common
3. **`order_date`** — date-range queries for reporting and recent orders

All three will be created with `CONCURRENTLY` — no transaction wrapping, no table locks, writes continue uninterrupted throughout.

